author: COMSOL
description: In this tutorial model, anisotropic turbulence in a hydrocyclone is simulated using the v2-f turbulence model. The complex swirl, which can be divided into an outer semi-free vortex and an inner core of solid body rotation, is captured as a result of the damping of turbulence fluctuations in the wall-normal direction. The velocity field and pressure drops between the inlets and the two outlets are both in qualitative and quantitative agreement with results from similar designs in the literature.
